{
    "name": "Assault Disintegrator Dragon",
    "type": "alien",
    "sections": [
        {
            "name": "Description",
            "type": "section",
            "html": "Artificial constructs that house dragon souls much like android bodies house those of humanoids, robot dragons are built as instruments of war. Each one is modeled around a specific category of weapon, such as laser blasters or projectile firearms, though far more specialized models exist. Perhaps the most infamous are the dreaded disintegrator dragons, massive engines of destruction built with nuclear fission chambers for hearts that enable them to unleash terrifying gouts of power that tear matter apart at the molecular level. Shock dragons, on the other hand, favor speed over destructive power and are often used as quick infiltrators and shock troops due to their mobility and ability to stun opponents. Sonic dragons are the most obscure, and they have the ability to harness raw sound into earsplitting blasts of incapacitating power."
        },
        {
            "name": "Robot Dragon",
            "type": "section"
        },
